{"title":"Cane Creek GXC is a Sleek, Lightweight Stem for Gravel or XC","link":"https://bikerumor.com/cane-creek-gxc-lightweight-stem-for-gravel-or-xc/","date":1730731121000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-hero-jpeg-e1730478778899.webp\" width=\"1280\" height=\"669\" alt=\"(Photos / Cane Creek)\" /></p>\n<p>Cane Creek’s latest product isn’t a <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/cane-creek-invert-gravel-suspension-fork/\" target=\"_blank\">groundbreaking gravel suspension fork</a> or a <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/cane-creek-collectors-edition-eebrakes/\">colorful rim brake</a>, but it is something that many bikes need. As far as Cane Creek’s lineup goes, this is one of their simpler products, but it looks like a cool, lightweight, and handsome stem, so let’s check out the details.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-stacked-jpeg-e1730478796560.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"665\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-stacked-jpeg-e1730478796560.webp\" alt=\"Cane Creek GXC Stem stacked\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-stacked-jpeg-e1730478796560.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-stacked-jpeg-e1730478796560-297x154.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-stacked-jpeg-e1730478796560-120x62.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-stacked-jpeg-e1730478796560-768x399.webp 768w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photos / Cane Creek)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s start with the weight. The GXC has a claimed weight of 96g for a 60mm stem. That’s a pretty light aluminum stem. The GXC is made from forged and machined 6066 aluminum and uses stainless steel hardware. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>GXC Claimed Weight</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>60mm: 96g</li>\n\n\n\n<li>70mm: 104g</li>\n\n\n\n<li>80mm: 112g</li>\n\n\n\n<li>90mm: 116g</li>\n\n\n\n<li>100mm: 120g</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>GXC Details</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The GXC sports “ghosted, laser etched” branding which looks low-key and attractive. Cane Creek GXC comes in polished black or polished silver. It’s a premium finish that would usually be on stems that could cost twice as much. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-angle-shot-jpeg-e1730478848587.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"398\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-angle-shot-jpeg-e1730478848587.webp\" alt=\"Cane Creek GXC Stem angle shot\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-angle-shot-jpeg-e1730478848587.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-angle-shot-jpeg-e1730478848587-297x92.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-angle-shot-jpeg-e1730478848587-120x37.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-angle-shot-jpeg-e1730478848587-768x239.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The new stem has an angle of +/- 6 degrees and is compatible with Cane Creek’s computer mount.  It has a stack height of 42mm and uses a 31.8mm bar clamp. It comes in five length options: 60mm, 70mm, 80mm, 90mm, and 100mm.   </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-gravel-side-view-jpeg.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-gravel-side-view-jpeg.webp\" alt=\"Cane Creek GXC Stem gravel side view\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-gravel-side-view-jpeg.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-gravel-side-view-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-gravel-side-view-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-gravel-side-view-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-gravel-side-view-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-gravel-side-view-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-gravel-top-view-jpeg.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-gravel-top-view-jpeg.webp\" alt=\"Cane Creek GXC Stem gravel top view\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-gravel-top-view-jpeg.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-gravel-top-view-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-gravel-top-view-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-gravel-top-view-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-gravel-top-view-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-gravel-top-view-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-XC-Side-view-jpeg.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-XC-Side-view-jpeg.webp\" alt=\"Cane Creek GXC Stem XC Side view\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-XC-Side-view-jpeg.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-XC-Side-view-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-XC-Side-view-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-XC-Side-view-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-XC-Side-view-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-XC-Side-view-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-XC-top-jpeg.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-XC-top-jpeg.webp\" alt=\"Cane Creek GXC Stem XC top\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-XC-top-jpeg.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-XC-top-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-XC-top-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-XC-top-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-XC-top-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Cane-Creek-GXC-Stem-XC-top-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Made specifically for gravel and cross-country mountain bikes, the GXC uses an aesthetic that “matches the overall size, shape, and proportions of modern gravel and cross-country frames. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>GXC Retail and Features</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Retail: $70</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Colors: Polished Black &amp; Polished Silver</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Lengths: 60mm, 70mm, 80mm, 90mm, and 100mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Angle: +/- 6 degree</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Bar Clamp: 31.8mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Steerer Clamp Height: 42mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Material: Forged and Machined 6066 aluminum alloy</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Hardware: Stainless Steel</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Graphics: Ghosted, laser-etched Cane Creek Logos</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Accessories: Compatible with Cane Creek Computer Mount</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Check the GXC Stem out as well as all of the cool bits at the link below. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://canecreek.com/\" target=\"_blank\">CaneCreek.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/cane-creek-gxc-lightweight-stem-for-gravel-or-xc/\">Cane Creek GXC is a Sleek, Lightweight Stem for Gravel or XC</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"16d0bacc3e08fc1d43586debf68e9fbce24c7bfd974b81393fbfe0cbaa60093a","category":"Cycling"}